com.tsgrp.migration.event.target

Class TranslateAttrListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tsgrp.migration.event.AbstractListener
      • com.tsgrp.migration.event.target.TranslateAttrListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SourceEndExportNodeEventListener, TargetBeginImportNodeEventListener

    public class TranslateAttrListener
extends AbstractListener
implements SourceEndExportNodeEventListener, TargetBeginImportNodeEventListener
    Inspects incoming migration nodes for attributes to be translated. If an attributes is contained in the injected attrNames lists, the listener uses the injected Rosetta object to translate the previous value to the updated value. The listener will also translate attrs on all associated nodes. (TODO: Make this optional?) Additionally, a list of translatedAttrNames can be injected. If this list is included, the original values in attrNames will not be changed and the translated values will be stored in the translatedAttrNames attributes.

      • setDefaultValue

        public void setDefaultValue(java.lang.String value)
        Injected, optional; if this value is injected, the value of an attribute with no translation will be defaulted to this value If this value is not injected, the translation will default to the original attribute value pre-translation as this was the original functionality and backwards compatability will be maintained. This value can not be used in conjunction with missedAttrsToFail.

      • setTranslateAllRepeatingAttrs

        public void setTranslateAllRepeatingAttrs(boolean value)
        Injected; if this value is true, this listener will attempt to translate each of a repeating attributes values and set those values back on the node. If false, it will use the first translation it finds and set that translation as the translated value (ignoring any other values).
